a sunken temple half-buried in the marshes
the fortified mountain pass known as [@place_name]
the [|legendary|forgotten|haunted] monastery of [@place_name], perched atop an unclimbable cliff
a vast underground necropolis whose entrance is disguised as a humble [@loc_type]
the [|overgrown|crumbling|half-flooded|scorched] ruins of [@place_name] — once the region's greatest city
a lighthouse at the edge of the world, no longer lit, that sailors still sometimes see from the sea

