Table: villain_role
a disgraced [|noble|general|high priest|archmage|guild master|judge] seeking revenge
a [|mad|grieving|corrupted|ambitious|desperate] [|wizard|warlord|cleric|rogue|noble|inquisitor]
the puppet master behind a [|thieves' guild|death cult|mercenary company|secret society|religious order]
an ancient [|vampire|lich|revenant|dragon|shade] posing as a [|merchant|advisor|scholar|noble|healer]
a demonically [|possessed|bound|created|summoned] [|knight|inquisitor|herald|oracle|champion]
a [|brilliant|ruthless|charismatic] [|general|spymaster|prophet] who genuinely believes they are saving the world

Table: villain_motive
to [|raise the dead|open a portal to the Abyss|destroy the old gods|break the wards on the prison plane|unmake the current age]
to avenge the [|destruction of their homeland|murder of their family|betrayal by a former ally|theft of something irreplaceable]
to achieve [|immortality|godhood|absolute power|the annihilation of a hated people|a peace that requires unthinkable sacrifice]
to fulfil an ancient [|pact|prophecy|oath|curse|debt] at any cost
to reclaim [|a stolen throne|lost magical knowledge|an artefact of immense power|a kingdom that no longer exists]
to bring about a [|new world order|golden age — for their kind only|purge of the weak|return of an era most consider best forgotten]
to prevent a catastrophe they alone have foreseen, by any means necessary

Table: villain_strength
Commands the loyalty of {1d4 + 2} powerful lieutenants.
Possesses an artefact that renders them [|immune to fire|impossible to scry|immune to mind magic|resistant to all weapons|impossible to kill permanently].
Has infiltrated the highest levels of [|the city guard|the temple|the merchant council|the king's court|the adventurers' guild].
Knows the true name of a [|demon|dragon|elemental|angel|lich] and can summon it once.
Has already won the first battle — the party starts on the back foot.
Controls the only [|bridge|port|pass|water supply|food supply|cure for a plague] into the region.
Has blackmail material on every notable figure in the region — no one will openly oppose them.
Is beloved by the common people, who will actively hinder any attempt to stop them.
Has prepared for this confrontation for [|decades|centuries|their entire life] — knows every move before it is made.

Table: villain_weakness
Bound by an ancient oath that prevents [|lying|harming children|entering sacred ground|acting on the new moon|crossing running water].
Obsessively loyal to one ally who could be turned against them.
Their power source can be disrupted by [|the light of dawn|a specific rune|running water|the sound of bells|iron|silver].
Haunted by genuine guilt; an appeal to conscience may give them pause.
Their lieutenants fear them but do not respect them — a show of weakness could shatter their army.
Relies entirely on a single powerful magical item; destroy it and they are mortal.
Their plan has a precise timetable; delay it long enough and it collapses entirely.
Cannot act in one specific location (sacred ground, a childhood home, a battlefield) — they have never explained why.
Has one person left they genuinely love; threatening that person is the only thing that gives them pause.

Table: villain_plan
assassinating [|the crown prince|the high priest|the archmage|the peace ambassador] before the summit
corrupting [|the water supply|the food stores|the holy relics|the city's wards] from within
gathering the [|final pieces of an ancient ritual|last of a destroyed bloodline|shards of a broken artefact]
turning the party's own allies against them, one by one
opening a rift to [|the Abyss|the Shadowfell|the Far Realm|a dead god's domain] beneath {location}
framing the party for a crime that will set two factions at war

